At the end of Steppenwolf Hesse has Mozart say twice to H.H. that he should learn to listen to the "radio music of life" and to appreciate the spirit behind it. Reminds you how R. Guenon used to listen to regular pop type music on the radio in his room instead of chants or such.

No matter what happens you must also enjoy your life. It sounds better when said during wartime or famine or something, but it is true regardless. Even if there are no gallows all humor is still gallows humor.
